# Icon Usage Rule

- When referencing an icon from a Figma design, use the `data-name` attribute in the Figma node to determine the icon name.
- Use [Phosphor Icons](https://phosphoricons.com/) by default for all icons.
- The icon component name in code should match the Figma `data-name` exactly (e.g., `ChartBar`, `Palette`).
- Always allow the displayed icon to be changeable via a prop or similar mechanism.
- Example:
  ```tsx
  import { ChartBar } from "phosphor-react";
  // ...
  <ChartBar />
  ```
- If a Figma icon does not exist in Phosphor, use a fallback or custom SVG, but prefer Phosphor whenever possible.
